entries.meaning: (uncountable, informal) Dirt or grime; any vague, messy, or unknown substance.
examples: I washed all the gunk off the light fixture, and found that it was white, not brown.

entries.meaning: (uncountable) A subculture of 21st century American males, combining elements of modern gothic culture with punk rock.
(countable) A member of the gunk subculture.

verbs.description: gunk (third-person singular simple present gunks, present participle gunking, simple past and past participle gunked)
